  "prompt": "What is a suitable solar panel installation provider in San Jose, California CA?",
  "response": "When looking for a suitable solar panel installation provider in San Jose, California, consider the following well-reviewed companies:\n\n1. **SunPower by Sea Bright Solar**:\n   - **Website**: [seabrightsolar.com](https://www.seabrightsolar.com/)\n   - **Overview**: SunPower by Sea Bright Solar is known for using high-quality SunPower panels, which are highly efficient and come with strong warranties. They have a solid reputation in the San Jose area and offer comprehensive services from consultation to installation.\n\n2. **SolarCity (Tesla Energy)**:\n   - **Website**: [tesla.com/energy](https://www.tesla.com/energy)\n   - **Overview**: As part of Tesla, SolarCity offers integrated solar solutions, including solar panels, batteries, and charging stations. They are well-known for their innovative approach and customer service.\n\n3. **PetersenDean**:\n   - **Website**: [petersendean.com](https://www.petersendean.com/)\n   - **Overview**: PetersenDean is one of the largest solar installation companies in the U.S. and has a strong presence in California. They offer a wide range of solar products and financing options.\n\n4. **SolarTech**:\n   - **Website**: [solartechonline.com](https://www.solartechonline.com/)\n   - **Overview**: SolarTech is a local company based in San Jose with a good reputation for quality installations and customer service. They offer customized solar solutions tailored to individual needs.\n\n5. **Sunrun**:\n   - **Website**: [sunrun.com](https://www.sunrun.com/)\n   - **Overview**: Sunrun is another major player in the solar industry with a strong presence in California. They offer various financing options, including leases and power purchase agreements (PPAs).\n\nWhen choosing a provider, consider factors such as:\n- **Reputation and Reviews**: Check customer reviews on sites like Yelp, Google, and the Better Business Bureau.\n- **Warranties and Guarantees**: Look for companies offering strong warranties on both the panels and the installation work.\n- **Financing Options**: See what financing options are available, including loans, leases, or PPAs.\n- **Experience and Certifications**: Ensure the company has experience in the San Jose area and that their installers are certified.\n\nIt's advisable to get quotes from multiple providers to compare prices, services, and overall value.",
